From support case:

Selecting and pasting a link to a wiki page (e.g., from a page tree hierarchy page) works nicely when editing a page in Word.  However, that link is of the form 

{code}
[http://wikiURL/display/key/Page+to+Link+to] (call this "Link Type 1")
{code}

The link works fine unless someone changes the name of the target page.  In such a case this type of link is not automatically updated by Confluence.

Links of the type

{code}
[key:Page to Link To] (call this "Link Type 2")
{code}
however, *are* updated by Confluence automatically, a great feature.

So I guess this request is either:

1) Modify Confluence to automatically update page links of Link Type 1, or
2) Modify the Office Connector to create links of Link Type 2.

